Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.71,0:00:10.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,恐龙曾统治地球...\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Dinosaurs ruled the planet 
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.55,0:00:12.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,(大卫爱登堡主持)
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.17,0:00:14.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...超过一亿五千万年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for over 150 million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.68,0:00:18.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,几乎在地球的每个角落 都可以找到它们的踪迹\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They occupied almost every corner of the globe
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.31,0:00:23.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而它们的体型和大小各异\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and came in almost every shape and size imaginable.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.35,0:00:27.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有些恐龙确实非常独特\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Some were truly extraordinary.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.82,0:00:34.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如今 我们知道霸王龙是游泳健将\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We now know that T. rex was a powerful swimmer...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.78,0:00:40.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,迅猛龙则是长着羽毛的狡猾猎手\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Velociraptors were cunning, feathered hunters,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.00,0:00:45.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有些恐龙的行为相当怪异\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and that some dinosaurs had the most bizarre behavior.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.84,0:00:52.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而 几乎每天都有新的发现\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But new discoveries are being made almost every day
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.59,0:00:57.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,揭示更多关于六千六百万年前 地球上生物的故事\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that tell us more about life on this planet 66 million years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.60,0:01:05.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,本季的《Prehistoric Planet》中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This time on Prehistoric Planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.48,0:01:08.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们将展示全新的动物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we reveal new animals
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.40,0:01:13.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,和关于它们寻找伴侣的新发现\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and new insight into their quest to find a partner,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.57,0:01:18.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,抚养一个家庭所面临的挑战\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the challenges faced by raising a family,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.49,0:01:21.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,以及它们间重量级的战斗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and their titanic battles.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.50,0:01:33.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,带领您穿越时光 探访大自然最壮丽的那个时代\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Journey to a time when nature put on its greatest show.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.51,0:01:41.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尽在《Prehistoric Planet 2》\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This is Prehistoric Planet 2.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.82,0:02:00.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}海洋\N第二季第四集
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.82,0:02:00.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs21}本WEB版外挂字幕由  {\c&H9B30FF&}风吹来的那片云{\c&HFFFFFF&}  双语合并
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.49,0:02:05.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海洋\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.87,0:02:10.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,史前地球上最大的栖息地\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The largest habitat on the prehistoric planet...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.42,0:02:18.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是曾在地球上生活过的最大掠食者的家园\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and home to one of the biggest predators that has ever lived...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.93,0:02:27.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,巨大的沧龙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a giant mosasaur.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.79,0:02:51.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但并不是所有的沧龙都是身长15米的怪物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But not all mosasaurs are ferocious 50-foot-long monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.96,0:02:56.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,躲在珊瑚礁之间的这条叫做磷酸盐龙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Taking refuge in the reef is Phosphorosaurus.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.47,0:03:00.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它也是沧龙的一种\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}She too is a mosasaur.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.26,0:03:04.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是最小的一种 身长不到3米\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}One of the smallest, at less than ten feet long.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.31,0:03:11.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它白天躲避危险\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}She spends the daylight hours hiding from danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.82,0:03:21.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但每个小时有一 两次 它就不得不迅速浮出水面换气\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But once or twice an hour, she has to dart to the surface to grab a breath.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.91,0:03:29.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,和所有沧龙一样 它是呼吸空气的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Like all of her kind, she is air-breathing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.09,0:03:39.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,和最大的沧龙相比 它就像个侏儒\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}She's dwarfed by the biggest mosasaurs.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.72,0:03:51.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但也是一个致命的掠食者\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But she too is a deadly predator...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.35,0:03:57.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也并不总是躲在阴影中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and she doesn't always hide in the shadows.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.03,0:04:03.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在正确的时机 它会摇身变成猎手\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When the time is right, she becomes a hunter.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.95,0:04:11.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个时机就是日落时分\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And that time is when the sun sets.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.77,0:04:35.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,随着夜幕的降临 它的水下世界发生转变\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}As darkness falls, her underwater world transforms.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.70,0:04:57.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这时 数以十亿计的生物 会从海洋深处上浮\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Now, billions of creatures will begin to rise from the depths
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.46,0:04:59.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,到海面附近来觅食\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to feed near the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.13,0:05:10.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球上规模最大的迁徙 是在几乎完全黑暗的环境中进行的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The largest mass migration on Earth occurs in almost total darkness
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.81,0:05:15.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,要想一睹其风采 我们只能借助特制的夜视摄像机\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and can only be seen with special night-vision cameras.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.19,0:05:27.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些夜间访客中最特别的是一种灯笼鱼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The most spectacular of these nighttime visitors are a type of lantern fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.29,0:05:37.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们那幽暗 诡异的光 是由其体内的化学反应发出的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Their faint, eerie light is produced by a chemical reaction inside their bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.76,0:05:49.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种生物发光的闪光可以用来迷惑掠食者\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A flash of this bioluminescence can be used to confuse predators.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.81,0:05:58.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从下方望去 这种光能让它们\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And when seen from below, the glow enables them to blend with
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.23,0:06:01.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,和洒满月光的海面融为一体 藏匿其中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and hide against the ocean's moonlit surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.78,0:06:10.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但它们躲不过磷酸盐龙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But they can't hide from Phosphorosaurus.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.49,0:06:18.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就其体型而言 它的眼睛是所有沧龙中最大的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}For her size, her eyes are the largest of any mosasaur...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.54,0:06:25.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能够看透幻象 识别猎物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}allowing her to see through the illusion and pick out her prey.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.78,0:06:48.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,到了黎明\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}By the time dawn arrives,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.78,0:06:52.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,迁徙的鱼群再次沉入深海\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the migrating shoal has sunk once more to the depths.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.08,0:07:01.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,磷酸盐龙也必须回到白天的藏身之处\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And Phosphorosaurus too must return to her daytime hiding place.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.30,0:07:10.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最大的沧龙回来觅食了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The biggest mosasaurs are back on the prowl.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.61,0:07:31.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它必须等到夜晚才能再次安全地捕猎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}She will have to wait till nightfall before it's safe to hunt again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.58,0:07:45.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,白天 史前的海洋 为另一种大为不同的猎手\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}By day, the prehistoric ocean provides opportunities
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.71,0:07:48.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,提供了机会\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for a very different type of hunter.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.72,0:07:56.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在北美洲温暖的浅海\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In the warm, shallow seas of North America,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.56,0:08:01.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,鱼的数量几乎和夜行灯笼鱼群一样多\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}fish numbers can almost match the nocturnal lantern fish shoal.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.24,0:08:16.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们对1.83米长的黄昏鸟有着巨大吸引力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And they are a magnet for six-foot-long Hesperornis.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.42,0:08:39.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,黄昏鸟虽然不会飞 但它已经完全适应了海洋生活\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Hesperornis may be unable to fly, but it's superbly adapted for ocean life.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.87,0:09:00.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,巨大 有力的双脚推动它非常迅捷地移动\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Large, powerful feet propel it with great agility.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.50,0:09:06.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,任何不走运的鱼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There's no escape for any unfortunate fish
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.79,0:09:10.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一旦被它满喙利如针尖的牙齿咬住 就不可能逃脱\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}once it's caught by this beak full of needle-sharp teeth.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.10,0:09:28.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,黄昏鸟独享鱼群的时间不长\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Hesperornis don't have the shoal to themselves for long.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.98,0:09:35.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,剑射鱼 又叫X鱼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Xiphactinus, known as X-fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.66,0:09:41.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,进食的机会很快吸引了一大群\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The feeding opportunity soon attracts them in large numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.04,0:09:53.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们身长超过5米 是海洋中最大 最快的鱼类之一\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}At over 17-feet long, they are one of the largest and fastest fish in the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.52,0:10:12.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,剑射鱼长着巨大的嘴 一次就能吞下好几条鱼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}With its huge mouth, Xiphactinus can scoop up several fish at once
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.65,0:10:16.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,甚至还能吞下体型是自己一半的猎物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and has even been known to swallow prey half its size whole.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.70,0:10:25.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一开始 食物足够所有掠食者吃的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}At first, there is plenty for everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.62,0:10:33.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但随着鱼的数量减少 X鱼的注意力转移了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But as fish numbers dwindle, the X-fish turn their attention elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.13,0:10:39.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,掠食者要变成猎物了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Predator is about to become prey.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.82,0:11:04.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,黄昏鸟只有一种选择:游泳逃命\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Hesperornis have only one option: to swim for their lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.93,0:11:24.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,剑射鱼的速度更快\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Xiphactinus is faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.22,0:11:29.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,黄昏鸟更敏捷\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Hesperornis is more agile.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.20,0:11:49.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但在X鱼眼中 万物皆可餐\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But in the eyes of an X-fish, anything is on the menu...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.04,0:11:56.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,甚至包括自己的同类\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}even their own kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.51,0:12:08.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,数分钟内 盛宴被消灭得干干净净\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Within minutes, the banquet is all but gone...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.73,0:12:13.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,掠食者们纷纷散去\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the predators move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.70,0:12:29.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海洋中的危险不仅仅只来自致命的猎手\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Danger in the ocean doesn't only come from deadly hunters.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.08,0:12:32.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也来自海洋本身\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It could come from the sea itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.97,0:12:46.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里是史前欧洲岛屿周边的海域\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Here, around the islands of prehistoric Europe,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.01,0:12:50.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,潮汐的力量给生物带来了挑战\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it's the power of the tide that creates challenges for life.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.10,0:12:56.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尤其是个头最小的家伙们\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Especially for the tiniest creatures.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.62,0:13:14.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些是菊石的卵\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}These are ammonite eggs.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.08,0:13:17.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,成千上万\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Thousands of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.38,0:13:25.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们被冲到靠近海岸的地方\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They have been swept inshore...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.06,0:13:31.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,岩石间的水坑里\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to rock pools.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.32,0:13:45.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这里 它们可以安全地成长\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Here, they have the chance to develop free from danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.83,0:13:53.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,卵很小 每个不到2厘米大\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The eggs are tiny, only a fraction of an inch each.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.79,0:14:01.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,卵中的小家伙们该破壳而出了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Now it's time for the young within to break free.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.60,0:14:15.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们通过喷射水流来移动\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They move by jet propulsion.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.98,0:14:19.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是掌握一项新的游泳技能并不容易\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But mastering new swimming skills is not easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.36,0:14:33.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,到目前为止 这些水坑提供了成长的温床\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Until now, these pools have provided a nursery.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.75,0:14:39.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但随着退潮 这些水坑被孤立起来\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But as the tide retreats, they become isolated.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.92,0:14:49.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其它生物可以逃离\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Others can make their escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.26,0:14:56.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但对于无助的菊石\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But for the helpless ammonites,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.23,0:15:00.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们成长的温床可能会迅速变成死亡陷阱\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}their nursery can quickly become a deadly trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.61,0:15:12.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在正午的阳光下 水坑里的水开始蒸发\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Under the midday sun, the water in the pool starts to evaporate.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.24,0:15:18.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果水完全干涸 它们全会死掉\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If it dries out completely, they will all die.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.04,0:15:25.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但还有希望\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But everything is not lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.30,0:15:30.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,小菊石可以做出壮举\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Baby ammonites can do something remarkable.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.84,0:15:36.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每一只都在努力追求自由 这迫使它们聚成一团\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Each makes its own bid for freedom, forcing them together.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.52,0:15:43.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,齐心合力让它们能够 作为一个整体有效地移动\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The combined effort means they effectively move as one.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.61,0:15:50.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每一只菊石都乘在这个微小的生命之浪上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Each is carried along on this tiny living tide,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.20,0:15:55.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,被身后的小伙伴们推上赤裸的礁石\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}pushed over the bare rock by those behind...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.83,0:16:04.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最终逃到较深的水中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}eventually escaping to deeper water.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.17,0:16:12.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在它们等着涨潮即可\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Now they wait for the rising tide.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.83,0:16:44.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但不是每一个菊石都能逃脱\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But not everyone escapes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.46,0:16:52.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,搁浅的不计其数\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Countless are left stranded...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.72,0:17:02.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,成为了食腐动物的美餐 比如这只火盗龙幼崽\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}food for scavengers, like these baby Pyroraptors.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.40,0:17:17.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其余的则被强大的洋流 带到了远离陆地数公里的地方\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The rest are carried by powerful currents many miles from land.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.33,0:17:28.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,甚至可以远达太平洋的中心\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Even as far as this, the very heart of the Pacific Ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.51,0:17:35.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些中央有泻湖的巨型环形珊瑚岛\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}These enormous atolls and the lagoons at their center
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.01,0:17:38.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是数千公里内唯一的庇护所\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}provide the only shelter for thousands of miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.23,0:17:52.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个罕见的地方是一种薄片龙 即蛇颈龙躲避危险的地方\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In this rare place, Tuarangisaurus, a kind of elasmosaur, finds safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.33,0:18:08.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但离开了这些浅水海域 情况就完全不同了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But outside these shallows, it's a different story.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.71,0:18:18.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,薄片龙每天都必须前往更深的海里\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Each day, the elasmosaurs must venture into deeper water.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.10,0:18:30.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,环状珊瑚岛峭壁上的峡谷 从浅海区通向丰饶的进食地\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Canyons in the atoll walls lead from the shallows to rich feeding grounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.82,0:18:38.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这一深海区域不仅吸引了饥饿的薄片龙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This deep water attracts not just the hungry elasmosaurs
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.74,0:18:42.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还引来了猎杀它们的掠食者\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but the predators that hunt them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.33,0:18:51.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海洋中最大的霸主\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The biggest in the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.67,0:18:58.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,身长15米的沧龙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}50-foot-long Mosasaurus.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.94,0:19:19.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从海底被带上来的营养物质 确保鱼的数量充足\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Nutrients driven up from the ocean floor ensure a plentiful supply of fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.66,0:19:29.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,薄片龙长着流线型的身体 和四个强大的鳍状肢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Streamlined bodies and four powerful flippers
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.71,0:19:32.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有着良好的机动性\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}give elasmosaurs great maneuverability.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.05,0:19:43.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但它们每天的觅食行动 让其移动模式变得可以预测\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But their daily feeding forays make their movements predictable
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.35,0:19:47.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,被一个聪明又耐心的猎手盯上了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for an intelligent and patient hunter.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.78,0:20:04.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,沧龙是一种依赖伏击的掠食者\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Mosasaurus is an ambush predator.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.41,0:20:15.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这只庞大的动物用巨大的尾巴 获得惊人的加速\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This enormous animal uses its huge tail to accelerate with astonishing speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.18,0:20:31.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这次不太走运\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This time, unlucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.53,0:20:44.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,事实上 大多数捕猎都会失败\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In fact, most hunts fail.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.20,0:20:50.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但这里生活着的薄片龙太多\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But with so many elasmosaurs living here,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.33,0:20:53.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,下一次机会很快就会出现\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it's not long before there is another opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.77,0:21:17.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,借着深色峡谷底的掩护 沧龙可以在没被看到的情况下靠近\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Camouflaged against the dark canyon floor, the mosasaur can approach unseen...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.78,0:21:23.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,等待一只年幼 没经验的猎物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}waiting for a young, inexperienced individual.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.82,0:21:26.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,完美的受害者\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The ideal victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.39,0:21:53.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,沧龙攻击猎物的力量如此之大\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Mosasaurus can strike their prey with such force
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.89,0:21:56.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,光是撞击就是致命的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that the impact alone can kill.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.40,0:22:04.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,袭击非常迅速 薄片龙几乎一定是毫无防备的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's an attack so swift, the elasmosaur almost certainly never saw it coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.95,0:22:16.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海洋里的生活很危险 不仅仅是因为这些巨兽\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Life in the ocean can be dangerous, not only because of giants.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.21,0:22:22.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在逃离了礁石水坑的小菊石中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Of the baby ammonites that escaped the rock pools,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.38,0:22:26.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在大海中存活几个月的不到百分之一\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}less than one in a hundred has survived several months at sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.85,0:22:32.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但这几只格外幸运\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But these few have been particularly lucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.27,0:22:38.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,洋流把它们带到了一个非常宜居的地方\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Ocean currents have carried them to an ideal place to live:
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.31,0:22:43.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,欧洲海岸线沿岸的海草床\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}seagrass beds off the coast of Europe.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.49,0:22:59.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这里 各菊石群的大小差异十分惊人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Here, shoals of ammonites occur in a surprising variety of sizes...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.42,0:23:01.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,什么形状都有\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and shapes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.32,0:23:28.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种长达1.83米的奇怪巨兽叫做杆菊石\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This strange, six-foot-long giant is Baculites,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.74,0:23:31.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们在海床附近觅食\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}which feeds near the seafloor.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.21,0:23:41.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尺寸几乎可以与之媲美的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And almost matching it in size,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.92,0:23:46.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,双菊石 形状像个巨大的回形针\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Diplomoceras, shaped like a giant paper clip.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.47,0:23:59.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们都在这里茁壮成长 因为食物充足\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They all flourish here, thanks to an abundance of food.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.02,0:24:07.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,浮游生物 小甲壳类动物 有些菊石甚至吃鱼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Plankton. Small crustaceans. Some even eat fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.75,0:24:22.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些小菊石开始形成\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}These hatchlings are beginning to acquire
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.33,0:24:26.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,成熟后将会拥有的奇特形状\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the extraordinary shape they will have when they are mature.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.55,0:24:33.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,突出的螺旋壳表明 这些是年幼的回角菊石\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The protruding spiral identifies them as young Nostoceras.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.85,0:24:42.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些是成年回角菊石\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}These are adult Nostoceras.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.06,0:24:47.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们喜欢较深水域的海床\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They favor the seafloor in deeper waters.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.63,0:25:14.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,菊石在史前海洋中蓬勃发展\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Ammonites have been thriving in these prehistoric oceans
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.22,0:25:17.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,时间几乎长达四亿年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for almost 400 million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.73,0:25:26.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其品种成千上万\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There are thousands of species.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.07,0:25:41.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,属于曾经存在过的最成功的一类动物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They are one of the most successful groups of animals to have ever lived...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.58,0:25:51.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,生生不息地活在温暖的温带海洋 甚至是两极最冷的水域\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}flourishing in the warm, temperate seas and even the coldest waters at the poles.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.85,0:26:02.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,比如这里 南极洲附近的冻海\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Like here, in the frozen sea around the Antarctic.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.11,0:26:19.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,经过了几乎全黑的一个冬季 低垂的太阳开始化冰\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}After a winter of near-total darkness, the low sun is beginning to melt the ice...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.20,0:26:25.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,使得这里可以再次接待 一种巨大的季节性访客\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}making it accessible once more for a giant seasonal visitor.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.46,0:26:34.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,莫特纳龙是一种奇怪的薄片龙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Morturneria, a strange type of elasmosaur.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.38,0:26:38.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们是暖血动物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They are warm-blooded,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.09,0:26:42.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,长着一层厚厚的脂肪来保存身体的热量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with a thick layer of blubber which conserves the heat in their body.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.15,0:26:52.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们是世界上最神秘 最难捉摸的动物之一\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They're one of the world's most secretive and elusive animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.11,0:27:01.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这群龙来自三千多公里外的南美洲\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This pod has migrated nearly 2,000 miles from South America
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.83,0:27:05.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,赶在春天来到这里\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to arrive here in time for spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.33,0:27:14.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是今年出生的小龙第一次遇见海冰\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's the first time this year's calves will have encountered sea ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.01,0:27:21.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这对呼吸空气的 爬行类动物来说可能是危险的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It can be dangerous for an air-breathing reptile.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.81,0:27:30.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们只能在冰面有破洞的地方换气\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They can only grab a breath of air where there are gaps in the ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.19,0:27:36.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,成年龙必须小心地寻找破洞\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Adults must navigate carefully to find them,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.03,0:27:39.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,幼龙必须紧随其后\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the youngsters must stay close.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.42,0:28:00.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些冰冷的水域为这些巨兽 最爱吃的食物提供了极佳的栖息地\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}These cold waters are an excellent habitat for this giant's favorite food.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.85,0:28:08.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,极地的泥巴里富含小生物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Polar mud full of small creatures.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.27,0:28:19.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每平方米的海床里 可能有成百上千的小型生物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There can be hundreds of tiny animals in every square foot of seafloor.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.16,0:28:30.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,把能吃的东西和黏糊糊的泥巴分开 是一个挑战\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Separating what's edible from the sticky mud is a challenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.13,0:28:36.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但它们有一种高效的解决方案\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But they have a neat solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.09,0:28:43.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,铲到一口泥后 它们会稍微合拢嘴巴\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Scooping up a mouthful, they partially close their jaws,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.30,0:28:49.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,制造出一个巨大的“筛子”来筛选食物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}creating a giant sieve to filter out the food.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.61,0:28:59.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只有这种动物演化出了如此用途的牙齿\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}These are the only animals to have evolved teeth to feed in this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.35,0:29:34.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,莫特纳龙会在这里饱餐整个夏天\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Morturneria will feed here all summer,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.77,0:29:38.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,直到极地的冬天将海面再次冻结\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}until the water ices over again in the polar winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.25,0:29:55.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在温暖的海域 它们会面对其他挑战\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In warmer waters, they will face other challenges.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.29,0:30:03.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但最足智多谋的动物们总能在史前地球\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But the most resourceful animals will always find opportunities
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.42,0:30:08.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,辽阔的大海里找到机会\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the vast oceans of the prehistoric planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.57,0:30:24.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,(揭秘《Prehistoric Planet》)
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.57,0:30:28.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,(沧龙的速度有多快 )
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.37,0:30:34.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,史前地球的陆地由恐龙统治\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The lands of the prehistoric planet were ruled by the dinosaurs.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.66,0:30:38.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但海洋则被一群大为不同的爬行动物占据\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But the seas were dominated by a very different group of reptiles:
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.96,0:30:40.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,沧龙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the mosasaurs.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.84,0:30:43.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这就是其中之一的头骨\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And this is the skull of one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.55,0:30:53.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,沧龙是海生蜥蜴\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Mosasaurs were seagoing lizards.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.31,0:30:57.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可以把它想成 会游泳的 鲸鱼般大小的科莫多龙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Think of a giant, swimming, whale-sized Komodo dragon.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.73,0:30:59.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,(加州大学 迈克尔哈比博士)
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.15,0:31:06.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,锥形的嘴 粗糙的皮肤 长着四个鳍而不是四肢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Tapered snout, rough skin, four fins instead of normal limbs
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.82,0:31:11.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,长长的尾巴很像上下颠倒的鲨鱼尾\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and a long tail that would look a lot like a shark tail but upside down.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.99,0:31:14.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这基本上就是沧龙了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's basically a mosasaur.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.29,0:31:22.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最大的是霍夫曼沧龙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The largest was Mosasaurus hoffmanni.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.01,0:31:26.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是一种依赖伏击的掠食者\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It was an ambush predator.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.84,0:31:30.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但它成功的秘诀是什么\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But what was the secret of its success?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.39,0:31:36.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们能在你眼前从完全静止状态\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They can move from just still, not moving at all
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.52,0:31:38.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,(南加州大学 基尔斯滕福莫索)
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.60,0:31:41.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,瞬间达到极快的速度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to incredible speeds right before your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.73,0:31:45.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在现代世界 诸如鳄鱼的爬行类动物拥有这种能力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In the modern world, we see this ability in reptiles like crocodiles.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.16,0:31:58.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们的肌肉能够提供 多次短促而强大的爆发\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Their muscles can deliver short bursts of tremendous power.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.92,0:32:04.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,鉴于沧龙是爬行类动物 是蜥蜴\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Mosasaurus, given that they're reptiles, given that they're lizards,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.84,0:32:07.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们的肌肉可能也有类似的能力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}probably had similar capabilities in their muscles.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.80,0:32:14.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们还有一种适应力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They also had another adaptation
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.01,0:32:17.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也许能增强出其不意的效果\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that could increase the element of surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.18,0:32:21.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,游泳的难点之一是\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}One of the tricky things about swimming is
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.90,0:32:25.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你需要一种特殊的动力来快速起动\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}you need a special kind of dynamic to get out of the gate quickly,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.27,0:32:28.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就好比短跑运动员从起跑器上起跑\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to do the equivalent of a sprinter's start from the blocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.32,0:32:33.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,达到这一目的的最佳做法 就是把身体弯成月牙形\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And one of the best ways of doing that is to bend yourself into a C-shape
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.82,0:32:36.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后用身体的一侧去推水\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and then push off of the water with the side of your body.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.95,0:32:40.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如今的鱼采用这一技巧\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Fish today use this technique.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.37,0:32:42.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,被称为“月牙起动”\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Known as a C-start,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.50,0:32:49.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它可以让鱼从静止不动 一瞬间加速到全速前进\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it allows them to accelerate from a standstill to full speed in an instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.05,0:32:50.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,(速度 加速 秒表)
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.42,0:32:53.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,沧龙可能会做非常相似的动作\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Mosasaurs likely were able to do something very similar,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.76,0:32:55.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当然 其体型要大得多\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but of course at a much grander scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.10,0:33:08.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那么霍夫曼沧龙这样的巨兽 到底能游多快呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}So, exactly how fast could a giant like Mosasaurus hoffmanni swim?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.53,0:33:16.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为了寻找答案 《Prehistoric Planet》 团队委托了一个独特的科学研究\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}To find out, the Prehistoric Planet team commissioned a unique scientific study.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.95,0:33:22.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,直到最近都不曾有人真正尝试\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Until recently, no one had really attempted to estimate
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.75,0:33:25.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,去详细地估测这些表现数据\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}these kinds of performance values in detail.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.88,0:33:27.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们是第一批真正试着\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Our work is one of the first attempts
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.67,0:33:31.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,把这些动物的能力量化的团队之一\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to really put numbers to the abilities of these animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.63,0:33:35.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,研究结果十分惊人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And the results we got from that are really pretty stunning.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.64,0:33:37.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,(身体长度)
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.35,0:33:40.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,团队计算了四次\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The team ran the calculations four times
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.52,0:33:41.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,(12吨 12.8米)
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.60,0:33:42.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,以确保结果正确\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to ensure they were correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.85,0:33:45.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,(尾部长度)
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.27,0:33:49.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,四次不同的测试得出了相同的总体结论\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}All four of the different trials came to the same overall conclusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.57,0:33:53.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些动物能够产生巨大的加速度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}These animals were able to generate massive accelerations.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.84,0:34:15.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这条沧龙游过其体长75%的距离\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This mosasaur, it could probably clear 75% of its body length
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.93,0:34:17.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也许只需一秒\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in one single second.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.76,0:34:23.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就是说如果那条沧龙离你17米远\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That means, if that mosasaur is 17 meters away from you,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.39,0:34:26.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一秒后 它就靠近了75%\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in one second, it will be 75% closer.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.90,0:34:29.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,第二秒后 它就会超过你\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And in the second second, it would have surpassed you
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.36,0:34:31.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可能顺便还把你吃掉了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and probably eaten you along the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.65,0:34:36.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,被一条沧龙撞到\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Being hit by a Mosasaurus would be
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.20,0:34:39.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有点像被一辆标准尺寸的半挂卡车撞\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a bit like being hit by a full-size semitruck.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.95,0:34:44.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,先不说之后被咬 光是沧龙的撞击\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Just the impact of the animal alone, much less the bite that would follow,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.37,0:34:48.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就能立刻杀死很多猎物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}would kill a lot of its prey instantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.42,0:34:54.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,沧龙的时速达到48公里\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Mosasaurs could reach 30 miles an hour
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.92,0:34:56.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只需一秒\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in as little as one second.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.93,0:35:07.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可以说 这就是为什么它们 是有史以来的终极海洋掠食者\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This is what makes them, arguably, the ultimate marine predator of all time.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.26,0:37:51.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,字幕翻译:谭萱

